  <div class='small-12 columns'>
    <p>
      <a href="/user_shifts">View your scheduled shifts here</a>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class='small-12 columns'>
    <ul id='activity-examples'>
      <li>
        Help place tables, chairs, canopies, signs, materials, trash and composting bins.
      </li>

      <li>
        Organize items, label and price as needed, collect money and tickets for items purchased, prepare root beet floats.
      </li>

      <li>
        Assemble orders, prepare sandwiches, etc. , collect money and tickets for meals.
      </li>
      <li>
        Bring a creative spirit and have fun!  Supplies and sample design inspirations are provided.
      </li>
      <li>
        This activity will make you laugh and get you wet.
      </li>
      
      <em><span class="brighten" data-redactor-tag="span">Ideal for parent and child team</span></em>
      <li>
        This activity is located at the sand box by the farmhouse and is a perennial favorite among the younger set.
      </li>
      <em><span class="brighten" data-redactor-tag="span">Ideal for parent and child team</span></em>
      <li>
        You will start and stop the music and give the winner a cake!
      </li>
      <em><span class="brighten" style="font-size: 1vw;" rel="font-size: 1vw;" data-redactor-tag="span">Ideal for parent and elementary child team</span></em>
      <li>
        Assist children as they assume new identities from Prairie Hill's expansive costume collection.
      </li>
      <em><span class="brighten" data-redactor-tag="span">Ideal for parent and child team</span></em>
      <li>
        Supervise, cheer, and assist children as they navigate a fun challenge course for young children.
      </li>
      <li>
        Supplies (pennies and cups) will be on hand. Stock cups as needed.
      </li>
      <em><span class="brighten" style="font-size: 1vw;" rel="font-size: 1vw;" data-redactor-tag="span">Ideal for parent and elementary child team</span></em>
      <li>
        Don a fun outfit with many pockets. Collect a ticket and invite the player to check a pocket.  Supplies (including outfit!) is provided.
      </li>
      <li>
        One person will take tickets, the other will get dunked! (you can swap spots). Bring a change of clothes.
      </li>
      <li>
        Collect cash ($2 per car; musicians and vendors park free) and direct cars to parking in the pasture. Dress for the weather. Bring a water bottle. We provide a chair, safety vest, and money aprons. Parkers will be stationed on highway 77 at the pasture entrance and in the pasture.
      </li>
      <li>
        Use your own camera and share the photos you take with the Fair Planning team to be distributed to the community.
      </li>
      <li>
        Someone ready to run from one end of the fair to the other as needed by various members of the fair committee.
      </li>
      <li>
        Take tickets. Volunteer will need some sense of how to throw a lasso.
      </li>
      <li>
        Collect tickets.
      </li>
      <em><span class="brighten" data-redactor-tag="span">Ideal for parent to volunteer with their young child</span></em>.
      <li>
        Count tickets, collect money, encourage raffle and fund raising package sales.
      </li>
      <li>
        Ideal for an Older Elementary or Adolescent student. Assist participants in drawing simple animals.  Samples will be provided.
      </li>
      <li>
        Assist children (with someone from Dixon Power Systems) as they get their hands wet creating energy.
      </li>
      <li>
        Assist Children (with someone from Lux) in creating their own button and bookmark designs.
      </li>
      <li>
        Adult volunteer to run corn cobbing machine. Will need to stay alert to assist children with cranking while keeping hands out of the machine.
      </li>
      <li>
        Assist children with monor injuries. Call EMS if needed. First aid supplies are included.
      </li>
    </ul>
